==English==
===Etymology===
{{F.}}, from {{L.}} ''[[limax]]'', snail

===Noun===
'''limaçon''' (''plural'' '''limaçons''')

#{{geometry}} A [[plane curve]] with [[polar equation]] <math>\rho = a + b\,\sin\,\theta</math> or <math>\rho = a + b\,\cos\,\theta</math>, of which the [[cardioid]] is a special case.

====Synonyms====
*[[limaçon of Pascal]]

